2 things to say:
1, Wilders team have shown categorically that they have been trying to set up with AJ for quite a while and AJ's team have always held it back, now Wilder has moved on to other fights Joshua has suddenly piped up.
2, Fury has accepted AJ's offer, but really it's just a mind game. I'm 100% sure Tyson won't want AJ hanging around his camp unless he's out to show AJ up in some way. Why would you want a future opponent to have an insight into your training camp? No sense in that at all and Fury ain't a fool.
